[% PROCESS header.tmpl title="Silver Lining Dashboard:  Manage ads" selected="adcenter" %]

<div id="main_content" class="grid_10 suffix_6">	
	<h2>Ad Center</h2>
	
	[% IF msg %]
		<p class="error">[% msg %]</p>
	[% END %]
	<div class="row">
		<p>This is where you manage the targeting of ads and messages on your Silver Lining routers.  Click on the links below to edit message bars or ad zones.While you can edit all of these items in this section, you will only be able to choose one of the three ad types for any given router (Twitter Feed, Text Entry, or Ad Invocation Code)
		</p>

		<ul class="bullet_list">
			<li><a href="[% base_uri %]/app/ad/twitter/index">Twitter Feed Message Bar</a> Use twitter in your message bar.</li>
			<li><a href="[% base_uri %]/app/ad/msg/index">Text Entry Message Bar</a> enter text messages in your message bar.</li>
			<li><a href="[% base_uri %]/app/ad/groups/list">OpenX Ad Zones</a> Add invocation code for your IAB standard ad banners.</li>

            [% IF reg.account_id.plan == 'free' %]
            <li>To brand your ad bar, you will need a paid account.  <a href="[% base_uri %]/billing/publisher/?plan=basic&email=[% reg.email %]">Click here</a> to sign up for our Basic Plan.</li>

            [% ELSE %]
			<li><a href="[% base_uri %]/app/ad/bugs/list">Branding Images</a> Brand your ad banners with your logo.</li>
            [% END %]
		</ul>		
		
	</div>
</div> 



[% PROCESS footer.tmpl %]
